Dow's 350-point rally led by gains in Chevron, Dow Inc. shares

Behind strong returns for shares of Chevron and Dow Inc., the Dow Jones Industrial Average is rallying Tuesday morning. The Dow DJIA, -0.31% was most recently trading 358 points, or 1.5%, higher, as shares of Chevron CVX, -0.09% and Dow Inc. DOW, -0.71% have contributed to the blue-chip gauge's intraday rally. Chevron's shares are up $3.19 (3.5%) while those of Dow Inc. have climbed $1.07 (3.2%), combining for a roughly 29-point bump for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are Pfizer PFE, +0.22%, Goldman Sachs GS, -0.27%, and Caterpillar CAT, -0.82%. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components equates to a 6.86-point swing.

